Descriptive Analysis and Preprocessing¶

Load raw data¶

We load and have a brief overview on our data

In [ ]:
# read data
df = pd.read_csv('../data/raw/fake_or_real_news.csv', usecols=['title', 'text', 'label'])
df['text'] = df['title'] + ' ' + df['text']
df.drop(columns=['title'], inplace=True)

real = len(df[df['label']=='REAL'])
fake = len(df[df['label']=='FAKE'])

print(f'{len(df)} total news')
print(f'real: {real} news')
print(f'fake: {fake} news')

Preprocessing¶

Text cleaning¶

Running a thorough cleaning process on our text, removing all unwanted characters and expressions such as symbols, urls... and such. Later on we will use a similar version of this preprocessing for the modelling phase, but feeding it into a pipeline

In [ ]:
df['text_clean'] = df['text'].map(lambda x: preprocessing(x))

Descriptive Analysis¶

We use function $eda$ to analyze:

  • Word count histogram: how many documents have N amount of words. Most documents below 2k words
  • Top 30 words: besides words that havent been picked up by our stopword detection, we can find some like $trump, clinton, state, campaign$ No big difference between true and fake news in terms of words used, atleast not visibly.
  • Most common bigrams ($donald trump$) and trigrams ($new york times$...)
